angle, resulting in the cup being pushed or knocked over instead of being
securely held. Additionally, the arm's positioning relative to the cup seems
slightly misaligned, which further contributes to the failure to establish a
stable grip. This misalignment and premature gripping action caused the task
to fail as the cup was not successfully picked up.
